{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate reductoisomerase synthesises 2-C-methyl-D-erythritol 4-phosphate from 1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate in a single step by intramolecular rearrangement and reduction and is responsible for terpenoid biosynthesis in some organisms [[cite:PUB00020977], [cite:PUB00099840]]. In Arabidopsis thaliana 1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate reductoisomerase is the first committed enzyme of the non-mevalonate pathway for isoprenoid biosynthesis. The enzyme requires Mn2+, Co2+ or Mg2+ for activity, with the first being most effective.</p>\n\n<p>The structure of this enzyme has been solved, showing the protein forms a dimeric assembly and contains a metal ion in the active site [[cite:PUB00099841]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "1r0k", "name" "Crystal structure of 1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate reductoisomerase from Zymomonas mobilis"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR036169", "name" "DXP reductoisomerase, C-terminal domain superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR30525" "1-DEOXY-D-XYLULOSE 5-PHOSPHATE REDUCTOISOMERASE"}, "hamap" {"MF_00183" "1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate reductoisomerase [dxr]"}, "pirsf" {"PIRSF006205" "1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate reductoisomerase"}, "ncbifam" {"TIGR00243" "1-deoxy-D-xylulose-5-phosphate reductoisomerase"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate reductoisomerase", "short" "DXP_reductoisomerase"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 76, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 8206, "taxa" 31802, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 38169, "sets" 0, "proteins" 38166, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 28712}, "pathways" 1}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"gp" {"displayName" "Genome Properties", "description" "Genome properties is an annotation system whereby functi